summary: An ordinance authorizing and directing the Corporation Counsel to dismiss John G. Barnes and his wife, and Kent Lumber Company, a corporation, as parties respondent in Cedar River Watershed Condemnation, under Ordinance No. 5803, of the City of Seattle, approved January 31, 1900, Cause No. 31510, in the Superior Court of the State of Washington, for King County and appropriating money out of the general fund to pay said respondents' costs in said proceeding.
